# hi-agent — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env` and edit. The binary auto-loads `.env` at startup (via
# `dotenvy`), but existing process env takes precedence — so production
# deployments injecting env via systemd / k8s / compose are unaffected.
# Everything below is optional — the agent runs with all of these unset.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Core
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Upstream LLM credential and base URL — injected by the local proxy, never
# written to disk in any claude/adapter config. AI_API_KEY is required;
# AI_API_BASE defaults to https://api.anthropic.com when unset.
# AI_API_BASE=https://api.anthropic.com
# AI_API_KEY=

# Cognition parameters handed to the bundled Claude adapter. All optional.
#   HI_AGENT_MODEL           → ANTHROPIC_MODEL on the adapter (unset = adapter default)
#   HI_AGENT_EFFORT          → settings.json effortLevel (e.g. low | medium | high)
#   HI_AGENT_PERMISSION_MODE → settings.json permissions.defaultMode (e.g. acceptEdits)
# HI_AGENT_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8
# HI_AGENT_EFFORT=high
# HI_AGENT_PERMISSION_MODE=acceptEdits

# Dev-only runtime override (point at an external node/adapter/claude to skip
# the first-run download — e.g. when developing offline). All three are
# required together. Debug use only.
# HI_AGENT_DEV_NODE=
# HI_AGENT_DEV_ADAPTER=
# HI_AGENT_DEV_CLAUDE=

# Override the runtime install cache dir (default: OS cache dir). On first run
# the pinned Node + ACP adapter + claude CLI are downloaded/installed here.
# HI_AGENT_RUNTIME_DIR=

# Logging filter — standard tracing-subscriber syntax.
# RUST_LOG=info

# MCP hub socket and shim binary. Override for split-binary / Docker layouts.
# HI_AGENT_MCP_SOCK=./data/mcp.sock
# HI_AGENT_SHIM_BIN=/path/to/hi-agent

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Voice — speech-to-text (POST /audio)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Set STT_PROVIDER=volcengine to enable transcription. With it unset, POST
# /audio returns 501.

# STT_PROVIDER=volcengine
# VOLCENGINE_STT_API_KEY=
#
# Defaults target doubao 2.0 (hours) on the recommended optimized (async)
# endpoint. Override if you have a different resource or endpoint:
#   hours      : volc.seedasr.sauc.duration   (default)
#   concurrent : volc.seedasr.sauc.concurrent
# VOLCENGINE_STT_RESOURCE_ID=volc.seedasr.sauc.duration
# VOLCENGINE_STT_ENDPOINT=wss://openspeech.bytedance.com/api/v3/sauc/bigmodel_async
#
# Speaker clustering/diarization (说话人聚类分离). On by default. For a posted
# clip (POST /api/in/audio) a ≥2-voice recording comes back as a labeled
# transcript ("说话人N：…" lines); a single-speaker clip is unchanged. On the
# live mic stream it runs as two-pass (二遍识别) — the low-latency partials that
# drive barge-in are preserved, and each finalized turn is tagged with a speaker
# id, which the built-in voiceprint (below) turns into "who". Set to 0/false/off
# to disable.
# VOLCENGINE_STT_SPEAKER_INFO=1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Voice — text-to-speech (speak channel="audio" → GET /audio)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Set TTS_PROVIDER=volcengine to enable synthesis. With it unset, the speak
# MCP tool rejects channel="audio" with an error string — the agent's
# reasonable next step is to retry with channel="thought".
#
# Uses the seed-tts-2.0 bidirectional-streaming V3 endpoint, authenticated with
# a single console API Key (X-Api-Key) — same scheme as STT above.

# TTS_PROVIDER=volcengine
# VOLCENGINE_TTS_API_KEY=
# VOLCENGINE_TTS_VOICE=zh_female_vv_uranus_bigtts
# VOLCENGINE_TTS_ENCODING=mp3
#
# Override only if you have a different model/billing tier or endpoint:
#   seed-tts-2.0 (default) | seed-tts-1.0 | seed-tts-1.0-concurr
# VOLCENGINE_TTS_RESOURCE_ID=seed-tts-2.0
# VOLCENGINE_TTS_ENDPOINT=wss://openspeech.bytedance.com/api/v3/tts/bidirection

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vision — image/video understanding (Doubao / Volcengine Ark)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Set VISION_PROVIDER=doubao to enable the capability. The OpenAI-compatible
# Ark Chat Completions endpoint understands image and video and returns text.
# It captions the vision channel: every posted still and every minute of the
# camera stream becomes a text description the agent reads (unset → a
# placeholder caption; the bytes are persisted either way).
#
# A preset picks model + reasoning behaviour in one knob; each field is
# independently overridable below.
#   fast      doubao-seed-2.0-mini   thinking=disabled  effort=minimal
#   balanced  doubao-seed-2.0-lite   thinking=auto      effort=medium   (default)
#   accurate  doubao-seed-2.0-pro    thinking=enabled   effort=high

# VISION_PROVIDER=doubao
# DOUBAO_VISION_API_KEY=
# DOUBAO_VISION_PRESET=balanced
#
# Overrides (each falls back to the preset's value):
# DOUBAO_VISION_MODEL=doubao-seed-2.0-lite
# DOUBAO_VISION_THINKING=auto          # enabled | disabled | auto
# DOUBAO_VISION_EFFORT=medium          # minimal | low | medium | high
# DOUBAO_VISION_API_BASE=https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Recognition — faces & voices (built-in, local; no API, no provider switch)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Unlike everything above, these are not cloud services with options — each is a
# single local ONNX model with nothing to choose. So there is no provider knob:
# the capability turns on when its model files are present and stays off (never a
# startup failure) when they aren't. Point at the files and it just works.
#
# What it does: recognition is soft evidence the agent weighs, never a verdict.
# Faces in posted stills and in the camera stream get a ⟨faces: …⟩ note; posted
# clips and live-mic speaker turns get a ⟨voice: …⟩ note. Unknown people are
# clustered ("先认人，后命名") under memory/facets/people/<id> at reflection time;
# the agent names an id from conversation (name_person) and fixes mistakes
# (merge_people). Identity = biometric cluster, decided by the agent.
#
# Face — InsightFace buffalo_l (SCRFD detector + ArcFace recognizer). Both files
# required to enable. Camera-stream faces additionally need `ffmpeg` on PATH
# (one keyframe per minute is decoded out); override the binary with FFMPEG_BIN.
# SCRFD_MODEL=./models/det_10g.onnx
# ARCFACE_MODEL=./models/w600k_r50.onnx

# Voice — CAM++ speaker embedding. The one file enables voiceprint.
# CAMPLUS_MODEL=./models/campplus.onnx

# Override the ffmpeg binary used for camera-stream keyframes (default: PATH).
# FFMPEG_BIN=/usr/bin/ffmpeg

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Imagery — image/video generation (Doubao / Volcengine Ark)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# The generation counterpart to Vision: a text prompt in, a picture or short
# video clip out. Image and video are independent capabilities with their own
# provider switch — enable either alone. Nothing calls these yet; they are
# built standalone, ready to wire into an emission path later.
#
# IMPORTANT: the base URL defaults to the **plan** endpoint (.../api/plan/v3).
# Do NOT point it at the plain .../api/v3 — the docs warn that bills as extra.

# --- Image (synchronous: one request, one image) ---
# IMAGE_GEN_PROVIDER=doubao
# DOUBAO_IMAGE_API_KEY=
# DOUBAO_IMAGE_MODEL=doubao-seedream-5.0-lite
# DOUBAO_IMAGE_API_BASE=https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/plan/v3

# --- Video (async task: submit, then poll until done) ---
# Models: doubao-seedance-2.0 (default) | doubao-seedance-2.0-fast | doubao-seedance-1.5-pro
# VIDEO_GEN_PROVIDER=doubao
# DOUBAO_VIDEO_API_KEY=
# DOUBAO_VIDEO_MODEL=doubao-seedance-2.0
# DOUBAO_VIDEO_API_BASE=https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/plan/v3
